
*** HOW TO INSTALL TRON LIBS

> INTRODUCTION

This document explains how to install tron libs for robotic control.

Software requirements:
- Linux environment
- Netbeans 8.1 for C++
- git

Components to be installed:
- libtron_talky.so	(standard language for communication between robotic control processes)
- libtron_comy.so	(library for inter process communication)
- libtron_tuly.so	(library for utilities)


> INSTALLATION


1. Download tron

git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron.git


2. Build tron_test project (in Netbeans)


3. Prepare to load required tron libs from everywhere:

touch tron_dady.conf
echo /path_to_tron/talky/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux > tron_dady.conf
echo /path_to_tron/comy/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux >> tron_dady.conf
echo /path_to_tron/tuly/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux >> tron_dady.conf
sudo mv tron_dady.conf /etc/ld.so.conf.d
sudo /sbin/ldconfig
(note: path_to_tron = tron installation path)


4. Prepare config files for tron logging:

see instructions in path_to_tron/logging/README_tron_logging file
(note: path_to_tron = tron installation path)





